  {
    "function_v0": {
      "doc": "Transfers the token with `token_id` from `from` to `to`.\\n\\nWARNING: Confirmation that the recipient is capable of receiving the\\n`Non-Fungible` is the caller's responsibility; otherwise the NFT may be\\npermanently lost.\\n\\n# Arguments\\n\\n* `e` - Access to the Soroban environment.\\n* `from` - Account of the sender.\\n* `to` - Account of the recipient.\\n* `token_id` - Token ID as a number.\\n\\n# Errors\\n\\n* [`NonFungibleTokenError::IncorrectOwner`] - If the current owner\\n(before calling this function) is not `from`.\\n* [`NonFungibleTokenError::NonExistentToken`] - If the token does not\\nexist.\\n\\n# Events\\n\\n* topics - `[\"transfer\", from: Address, to: Address]`\\n* data - `[token_id: u32]`",
      "name": "transfer",
      "inputs": [
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "from",
          "type_": "address"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "to",
          "type_": "address"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "token_id",
          "type_": "u32"
        }
      ],
      "outputs": []
    }
  },
  {
    "function_v0": {
      "doc": "Transfers the token with `token_id` from `from` to `to` by using\\n`spender`s approval.\\n\\nUnlike `transfer()`, which is used when the token owner initiates the\\ntransfer, `transfer_from()` allows an approved third party\\n(`spender`) to transfer the token on behalf of the owner. This\\nfunction verifies that `spender` has the necessary approval.\\n\\nWARNING: Confirmation that the recipient is capable of receiving the\\n`Non-Fungible` is the caller's responsibility; otherwise the NFT may be\\npermanently lost.\\n\\n# Arguments\\n\\n* `e` - Access to the Soroban environment.\\n* `spender` - The address authorizing the transfer.\\n* `from` - Account of the sender.\\n* `to` - Account of the recipient.\\n* `token_id` - Token ID as a number.\\n\\n# Errors\\n\\n* [`NonFungibleTokenError::IncorrectOwner`] - If the current owner\\n(before calling this function) is not `from`.\\n* [`NonFungibleTokenError::InsufficientApproval`] - If the spender does\\nnot have a valid approval.\\n* [`NonFungibleTokenError::NonExistentToken`] - If the token does not\\nexist.\\n\\n# Events",
      "name": "transfer_from",
      "inputs": [
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "spender",
          "type_": "address"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "from",
          "type_": "address"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "to",
          "type_": "address"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "token_id",
          "type_": "u32"
        }
      ],
      "outputs": []
    }
  },
  {
    "function_v0": {
      "doc": "Gives permission to `approved` to transfer the token with `token_id` to\\nanother account. The approval is cleared when the token is\\ntransferred.\\n\\nOnly a single account can be approved at a time for a `token_id`.\\nTo remove an approval, the approver can approve their own address,\\neffectively removing the previous approved address. Alternatively,\\nsetting the `live_until_ledger` to `0` will also revoke the approval.\\n\\n# Arguments\\n\\n* `e` - Access to Soroban environment.\\n* `approver` - The address of the approver (should be `owner` or\\n`operator`).\\n* `approved` - The address receiving the approval.\\n* `token_id` - Token ID as a number.\\n* `live_until_ledger` - The ledger number at which the allowance\\nexpires. If `live_until_ledger` is `0`, the approval is revoked.\\n\\n# Errors\\n\\n* [`NonFungibleTokenError::NonExistentToken`] - If the token does not\\nexist.\\n* [`NonFungibleTokenError::InvalidApprover`] - If the owner address is\\nnot the actual owner of the token.\\n* [`NonFungibleTokenError::InvalidLiveUntilLedger`] - If the ledge",
      "name": "approve",
      "inputs": [
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "approver",
          "type_": "address"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "approved",
          "type_": "address"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "token_id",
          "type_": "u32"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "live_until_ledger",
          "type_": "u32"
        }
      ],
      "outputs": []
    }
  },
  {
    "function_v0": {
      "doc": "Approve or remove `operator` as an operator for the owner.\\n\\nOperators can call `transfer_from()` for any token held by `owner`,\\nand call `approve()` on behalf of `owner`.\\n\\n# Arguments\\n\\n* `e` - Access to Soroban environment.\\n* `owner` - The address holding the tokens.\\n* `operator` - Account to add to the set of authorized operators.\\n* `live_until_ledger` - The ledger number at which the allowance\\nexpires. If `live_until_ledger` is `0`, the approval is revoked.\\n\\n# Errors\\n\\n* [`NonFungibleTokenError::InvalidLiveUntilLedger`] - If the ledger\\nnumber is less than the current ledger number.\\n\\n# Events\\n\\n* topics - `[\"approve_for_all\", from: Address]`\\n* data - `[operator: Address, live_until_ledger: u32]`",
      "name": "approve_for_all",
      "inputs": [
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "owner",
          "type_": "address"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "operator",
          "type_": "address"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "live_until_ledger",
          "type_": "u32"
        }
      ],
      "outputs": []
    }
  },
  {
